thread.title_full: Dogs initially thought to have been chemically burned in Lancaster may have sunburns - Worldnews.com

author: wn.com
title: Dogs initially thought to have been chemically burned in Lancaster may have sunburns
text: At least 7 dogs have been found, or brought to local shelters, with what appears to be chemical burns on their backs. The L.A. County Board of Supervisors is offering a $25,000 reward for information leading to the arrest and/or conviction of a suspect in connection with apparent chemical attacks involving domestic dogs in the Antelope Valley and surrounding communities. (Photo courtesy of Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department)
